{
  "doc_id": "37915",
  "text": "Some non-lymphoid tissues, such as lung, kidney and small intestine express mGITR mRNA (Table 2) . GITR expression was detected also on osteoclast precursor cells, keratinocytes and retinal pigment epithelial (RPE) cells [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . A similar (though not perfectly matched) pattern of expression was described in humans. hGITR mRNA was expressed at a good level in lung and, at a low level, in brain, kidney and liver [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . It was also found in a colorectal adenocarcinoma cell line [CITATION_6] . In summary, GITR is mainly expressed in hematological cells, but there is some evidence that it is also expressed in non-lymphoid tissues. Other TNFRSF members sharing structural properties with mGITR, such as 4-1BB, although expressed mainly in lymphoid organs are also found in some non-lymphoid cells such as lung [CITATION_7] .",
